<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-7212] Bean Validator should use OSGi-friendly ValidationProviderResolver if deployed into OSGi environment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-7212</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If Bean Validator is deployed into OSGi container (like Karaf), it should use OSGi-friendly &lt;tt&gt;ValidationProviderResolver&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should detect the type of the current &lt;tt&gt;CamelContext&lt;/tt&gt; and if the latter is OSGi-aware, and if &lt;tt&gt;ValidationProviderResolver&lt;/tt&gt; isn&apos;t specified explicitly, then we should use &lt;tt&gt;HibernateValidationProviderResolver&lt;/tt&gt; (which is OSGi-friendly).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
